      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZERO KILLER (1) showed good speed off a low draw and there throughout but run over late when 7th over 400m at Warragul in a Mix 3/4. Can make amends. PAW BASTOW (6) jumped well from the low draw and led all the way to score last start (22.17) at Warrnambool in a Grade 5 over 390m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Form should stack up. HOW AWESOME (2) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at Ballarat over 390m behind Big Boy Pants (22.46) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings five times from five starts. Worth following up. ZIPPING NUTTALL (7) was in the money last time at this track (20.19) in a Grade 5, finishing a 2 length second. Already a winner from this draw.",
